ttps://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-6-0-1/\">Events Calendar Pro 6.0.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3692:\"\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of Events Calendar Pro reformats event recurrence and date-related meta before migration to fix a number of migration warnings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-new\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> New</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">New features included in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Added a link to convert an Event to single in the Events Manager and Series edit screens.</li><li>Added some explanatory text to the Single Update option.</li><li>Prevent conflicts with the WooCommerce product page shortcode when in the editor.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Corrected some translation domains pointing to the wrong plugin.</li><li>Corrected a mismatch between the <code>get_terms</code> filter and our hooked function signature.</li><li>Normalize and reformat event recurrence and date-related meta before migration to fix a number of migration warnings.</li><li>Fix regression that was making the Events Calendar Pro tabs show up on the Event Tickets settings.</li><li>Ensure we don&#8217;t try to check nonexistent globals ($_POST, $_GET, etc).</li><li>Corrected a Block Editor fatal error.</li><li>Fixed a fatal in the mini-calendar widget.</li><li>Ensure that taxonomies get carried over when splitting recurring events.</li><li>Ensure recurring events have a series generated for them when one is not specified.</li><li>Prevent duplicated JOINs on View Series filters.</li><li>Prevent editing the first occurrence of a recurring event from creating a new event.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>6 new strings added</li><li>130 updated</li><li>1 fuzzied</li><li>2 obsoleted</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-6-0-1/\">Events Calendar Pro 6.0.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"The Events Calendar 6.0.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:161:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-0-1/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 22 Sep 2022 18:08:29 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2472080\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:639:\"<p>&#160; Summary Maintenance Release This latest version of The Events Calendar rebuilds event-related metadata to fix a number of migration preview failures. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✨ New New features included in this release: We&#8217;ve added some helpful knowledgebase article links&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-0-1/\">The Events Calendar 6.0.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3778:\"\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of The Events Calendar rebuilds event-related metadata to fix a number of migration preview failures.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-new\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> New</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">New features included in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>We&#8217;ve added some helpful knowledgebase article links to the CSV import screen.</li><li>Ensure the Fast-forward link uses the correct, customizable color as other links.</li><li>Include Custom Tables Migration in the Support System Information array.</li><li>Added compatibility for the new &#8220;Convert to single&#8221; option in Events Calendar Pro.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Prevent network deactivation from overwriting the subsite settings with main site cached settings.</li><li>We&#8217;ve corrected some text domains.</li><li>Ensure the details in the single event page are accurate for Divi users who set any Divi template under Settings → Events template.</li><li>Add caching to prevent duplicated queries for translated venue/organizer values. (Props to @dgwatkins for the suggested fix!)</li><li>Check the document for <code>lang</code> and <code>rtl</code> attributes and pass them on to the datepicker, so it adapts properly.</li><li>Normalize, reformat, and rebuild event date-related meta to fix a number of migration preview failures.</li><li>Corrected a problem with moving tickets when Events Calendar Pro is not active.</li><li>Corrected an issue with migrating past events that straddle Daylight Savings Time.</li><li>Fixed the Community Events recurrence link.</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>5 new strings added</li><li>163 updated</li><li>0 fuzzied</li><li>0 obsoleted</li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-0-1/\">The Events Calendar 6.0.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"6 Ideas for An Engaging Event Series\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:160:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/6-ideas-for-an-engaging-event-series/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Sep 2022 14:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2472288\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:623:\"<p>Whether you&#8217;re a business owner, a marketer, or an event planner, getting people to care about your events can be hard work—especially when you want to drive interest in an event series. Building an event series often relies on keeping your audience engaged during each event. Engagement helps folks feel pulled to come back again&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/6-ideas-for-an-engaging-event-series/\">6 Ideas for An Engaging Event Series</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Rachel Kolman\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6402:\"\n<p>Whether you&#8217;re a business owner, a marketer, or an event planner, getting people to care about your events can be hard work—especially when you want to drive interest in an event series. Building an event series often relies on keeping your audience engaged during each event. Engagement helps folks feel pulled to come back again to the next one.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s no better way to keep attendees engaged than by mixing in fun activities. While a deeper objective may be to present important information or teach something new, you should also ensure your audience has fun at the same time.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are six creative ways to add excitement and increase engagement for your next event series.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1. <strong>Liven up your event series with a theme.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A theme can be an excellent tool for an event series. It can build community, create a consistent experience, and build relationships. Here are some examples of themes that can tie together events across a series:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>A historical period.</strong> You might have several events that are all themed around different decades or historical periods. For example, you could have a 1940s-themed event series based around classic Americana with big band music and vintage fashion.</li><li><strong>A favorite snack food or restaurant chain.</strong> Consider holding an event featuring one of your favorite foods at the end of each month as part of your regular event series. This will encourage guests to come back month after month for more treats!</li><li><strong>A travel destination (or two).</strong> Of course, who doesn’t love a tropical destination themed-event? This instantly evokes a sense of fun and can even conjure up a positive association. Mix it up and try a new far-off travel destination at each event to keep guests itching to come back.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>2. <strong>Put together a speaker series.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A speaker series is a great way to provide a variety of content for your audience. A speaker series is especially effective if you want to explore multiple facets of one topic through different perspectives. Multiple presenters can offer unique takes on a given subject. Conversations can change from week to week, giving attendees a reason to keep coming back.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When booking speakers for an event series with multiple events, consider whether each event should have its own theme or whether all events should be based around one central theme or topic. For example, if your event series is an alumni networking event, consider honoring a different graduating class or a niche area of study with each event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>3. Bring your audience to different locations, virtually or in person<strong>.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Get your audience out of the office and into the world. Consider traveling around your city and hosting each event in the series at a different location. Guests will love the excuse to explore and mix business with pleasure.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re planning a virtual event, showcase different countries via video conferencing backgrounds or themed dress codes on camera. The possibilities here are endless.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>4. <strong>Combine virtual and in-person events into a series.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In this model, each event has a combination of an in-person and a virtual component. For example, a live crowd could be watching a presentation delivered via a conferencing tool, with a live Q&amp;A after. Or, attendees who can’t make an in-person event can watch a live feed. They can interact in chat with a live, onsite moderator to feel included.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These types of events can be hosted by a variety of different platforms (such as Facebook groups, Zoom, or Slack channels), but they should have some sort of structure or outline that stays consistent in each event in the series.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>5. <strong>Use a series as drip content delivery.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Event series are not just great for building your community–they can also be used as a delivery mechanism for any type of content you have created.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you have a course that would be valuable for your audience, you can create an event that includes the free portion of the course (typically called “the teaser”), and then offer it up at the end as part of an invitation to join the rest of your paid program.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use an event series to create webinars or coaching programs around topics like mindset or goal setting.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>6. <strong>Curate events for customer niches.</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Curated events are unique to your business, your customers, and even you as a person. This is something that should be reflected in the events you host.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you&#8217;re a tech company and want to host an event for parents who work in the digital space, then maybe it would make sense to partner with other companies that help parents find new ways of working from home.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you set up these types of curations and partnerships as event series, you give yourself the opportunity to diversify your business and clientele.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-conclusion\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you think of a series as a way to deliver information or entertainment, then it becomes more than just another marketing tactic—it becomes part of your brand identity. Folks will come to rely on you for meaningful and engaging content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To help you build a series of engaging events, The Events Calendar’s Pro 6.0 release features a new process for creating recurring events and a new post type called <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-the-events-calendar-6-0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Series</a>. You’ll be able to duplicate any event – single or recurring – with the same content and settings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to try it out for yourself? You can play around with these new features first in our <a href=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/demo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">live demo</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/6-ideas-for-an-engaging-event-series/\">6 Ideas for An Engaging Event Series</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"Featured Calendar: Sydney World Pride\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:171:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-sydney-world-pride/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 13 Sep 2022 11:05:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"WordPress Calendar Examples\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2467534\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:694:\"<p>Our next WordPress calendar example comes from Sydney, Australia to celebrate the global LGBTQIA+ community. Sydney World Pride is an upcoming 2023 not-for-profit festival. This website incorporates the events of Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras, ​​plus a broader festival offering across arts, sports, theatre, concerts, parties, First Nations programming, and a human rights conference.  &#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-sydney-world-pride/\">Featured Calendar: Sydney World Pride</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14340:\"\n<p>Our next WordPress calendar example comes from Sydney, Australia to celebrate the global LGBTQIA+ community. <a href=\"https://sydneyworldpride.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sydney World Pride</a> is an upcoming 2023 not-for-profit festival. This website incorporates the events of <a href=\"https://www.mardigras.org.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras</a>, ​​plus a broader festival offering across arts, sports, theatre, concerts, parties, First Nations programming, and a human rights conference.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sydney World Pride uses <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Events Calendar</a> plugins to showcase all their festival events and to gather excitement about the global Pride celebration starting in February 2023. Let’s take a look at how they accomplished this exceptional feat below.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-a-colorful-homepage\">A colorful homepage</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Sydney World Pride’s homepage engages its audience right from the start. With on-brand colors and a vibrant theme choice, prospective attendees can get a sense of the kind of events that they’ll be attending. The slider in the header features informative sections, including one that links users to all their upcoming events.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"708\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023.png\" alt=\"Featured Calendar: Sydney World Pride homepage\" class=\"wp-image-2467535\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023.png 708w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-133x300.png 133w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-453x1024.png 453w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-38x85.png 38w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-680x1536.png 680w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-430x972.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-645x1458.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-460x1040.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-512x1157.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-488x1102.png 488w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-235x530.png 235w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-300x678.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-354x800.png 354w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-500x1130.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 708px) 100vw, 708px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Beyond that, there’s a custom-built section with a few of the featured upcoming events and another link to view all upcoming events. What’s cool about this website is that it mainly focuses on showcasing its events as the main feature. Since the festival is only once every few years, Sydney World Pride seems to be going all out to make sure that their events shine. This means that more site visitors may purchase tickets to their festival.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"531\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1.png\" alt=\"Upcoming events in our WordPress calendar example\" class=\"wp-image-2467536\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1.png 531w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-100x300.png 100w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-340x1024.png 340w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-28x85.png 28w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-510x1536.png 510w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-430x1296.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-460x1386.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-512x1543.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-366x1102.png 366w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-176x530.png 176w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-300x904.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Home-Page-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-1-500x1507.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 531px) 100vw, 531px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Being that the events are the stars of the show, the events page is easy to navigate to any page on the website. From the homepage, you can find the main calendar page from the navigation bar item titled <a href=\"https://sydneyworldpride.com/events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Explore Events</strong></a> at the top of the page, an option in the slider in the header, or you can select the <strong>View All</strong> option in the custom events widget. You can’t miss this amazing calendar! </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-an-electrifying-calendar-page\">An electrifying calendar page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>And now it’s time for the main event! The calendar page maintains the same styles as the rest of the website and includes a customized version of our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-calendar-filter-bar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Filter Bar</a> plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"953\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM.png\" alt=\"Calendar page created with The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2467537\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM.png 1600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-300x179.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-665x396.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-140x83.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-768x457.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-1536x915.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-688x410.png 688w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-344x205.png 344w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-1032x615.png 1032w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-430x256.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-645x384.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-1068x636.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-460x274.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-1074x640.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-512x305.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-707x421.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-600x357.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.44.40-PM-500x298.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The calendar view by default is List View, but users can also switch over to Map View, which is one of the premium views available with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro</a>. Sydney World Pride also transformed its <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/featured-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Featured Events</a> into Official Events, with an eye-catching unique border. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/event-categories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event categories</a> also show up in the filter bar so site visitors can sort through events by category.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"801\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM.png\" alt=\"Map View calendar page in our latest WordPress calendar example\" class=\"wp-image-2467538\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM.png 1600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-300x150.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-665x333.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-140x70.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-768x384.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-1536x769.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-430x215.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-645x323.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-1068x535.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-460x230.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-1074x538.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-512x256.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-707x354.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-600x300.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-08-01-at-12.52.12-PM-500x250.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-a-stunning-single-event-page\">A stunning single event page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The single event page includes a larger header, followed by an event description. Below that, you’ll find the Classic Event Details block, containing all the information you need to find the event. Further down, you can add the event to your personal Google Calendar or iCalendar with the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/exporting-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">export function</a> available with The Events Calendar. Lastly, towards the bottom of the page, the related events are listed for site visitors to click on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"410\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-410x1024.png\" alt=\"Single event page in our featured calendar \" class=\"wp-image-2467539\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-410x1024.png 410w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-120x300.png 120w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-34x85.png 34w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-430x1075.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-460x1150.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-512x1280.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-441x1102.png 441w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-212x530.png 212w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-300x750.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-320x800.png 320w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023-500x1250.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/09/Pink-Salt-Sydney-WorldPride-2023.png 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 410px) 100vw, 410px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-try-the-events-calendar-today\">Try The Events Calendar today!</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://sydneyworldpride.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sydney World Pride</a> created such a celebratory WordPress calendar example, and you can too! There is no end to the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/category/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">different types of events</a> that work well with our plugins. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If we’ve piqued your interest with this stunning example, but you’re not quite ready to take the plunge, have no fear. Try out all our products at no risk by spinning up <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">your own demo site</a> to take our plugins for a test drive first. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-sydney-world-pride/\">Featured Calendar: Sydney World Pride</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"\n	1	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:13:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Tue, 27 Sep 2022 05:34:32 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:6:\"cf-ray\";s:20:\"7511deebe990350e-ICN\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"7a86cc5c2767f51f364d091200c95964\"\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Fri, 23 Sep 2022 19:26:45 GMT\";s:4:\"link\";s:117:\"<https://theeventscalendar.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\", <https://theeventscalendar.com/>; rel=\"canonical\"\";s:4:\"vary\";s:15:\"Accept-Encoding\";s:15:\"cf-cache-status\";s:6:\"BYPASS\";s:10:\"cf-apo-via\";s:11:\"origin,feed\";s:13:\"cf-edge-cache\";s:24:\"cache,platform=wordpress\";s:9:\"x-nocache\";s:1:\"1\";s:6:\"server\";s:10:\"cloudflare\";s:7:\"alt-svc\";s:43:\"h3=\":443\"; ma=86400, h3-29=\":443\"; ma=86400\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20220901015420\";}', 'no');
